key ingredients to an effective preventive program . 4 . patient education . the dental hygienist will be responsible for ensuring that patients receive necessary educational counseling of preventive xanterra parks & resorts believes people are our most valuable resource . our success depends upon highly_motivated , committed , and competent people who share our vision and work together to attain it , while our work_environment encourages responsibility for personal growth and promotes pride in each employee . we foster a culture that promotes fairness and diversity , and provides equal opportunities throughout the organization . working at any one of our locations is not just a job , but also an experience of a lifetime . after a day s work , there is so much to do and see at any of our locations . let your talents get you here , then take advantage of all the splendor our parks and resorts offer . welcome to the coolest culinary job in the desert - furnace creek resort in death valley national park is searching for an executive chef to lead its many varied operations at 214 feet below sea level . the ideal candidate is an energetic , mentoring chef who understands high_volume / seasonal operations ; has a solid understanding of financial expectations and ensuing internal controls ; and is an inspirational leader . as a leader in sustainable offerings within the national park system , the creativity in designing seasonal menus , understanding national trends , and sourcing both local and sustainable products will be paramount to the success of the executive chef . this position reports to the director of f & b ; and will be required to engage and effectively communicate with committees and other management_team members pursuant to food and beverage programming , ideas and events . the executive chef will be personable , enthusiastic , accessible and appropriately visible to engage with the membership and be receptive and responsive to feedback and suggestions . primary_responsibilities include but are not limited to : all menu development , recruiting and developing an excellent culinary team ; scheduling and supervision ; training , recipe standards , and nutritional analysis of menu items ; inventory , labor and cost control and budget development / management ; purchasing ; and execution of special events and private functions . . ideal candidates will not only have a background that illustrates a logical career progression as well as passion , a culinary degree , and various certifications , but also have experience in high_volume environments as our restaurants and outlets operate at full capacity during the height of the busy season . the executive chef should also embody the spirit of working in the beauty of the national park system .
